Panic has continued to rise in Ute-Okpu and Idumuesah communities in Ika North East Local Government Area of Delta State following mysterious deaths in the two communities. The two communities had last week recorded fifteen strange deaths. The victims were between the ages of 18 and 25.  The death toll, which has risen to thirty as of Monday in the area, followed the death of a son and daughter of a middle-aged woman, Monica Emeke, who were between the ages of 22 and 26. They purportedly vomited blood before they gave up the ghost. The cause of the deaths had not been established, but SaharaReporters gathered that it could be an outbreak of a disease. See Also






